{{see|minister}}

==German==
===Pronunciation===
* IPA: /mɪˈnɪ.stɛr/

===Noun===
'''Minister''' {{m}} (''plural'' '''Minister''', ''genitive'' '''Ministers''')
# A person who is commissioned by the government for public service
#* Johannes Schmidt ist der Minister für Nationale Verteidigung.
#** Johannes Scmidt is the Minister of National Defence.

====Usage notes====
Only used for males.  For females, use [[Ministerin]] {{f}}.

====Derived terms====
* [[Ministerin]], feminine form of Minister.

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[minister#Dutch|minister]] ''m,f.''
*English: [[minister]]
*Finnish: [[ministeri]]
*French: [[ministre]] ''m,f.''
*Indonesian: [[menteri]]
*Japanese: [[大臣]] (だいじん, daijin)
*Old English: [[þegen|þeġen]]

